					<msContents>
						<summary>

						<p>This registers the gift by the king, of the village Mēlai-Koḍumaḷūr <hi rend="italic">alias</hi> Uttama-Pāṇḍyanallūr excluding the lands already being enjoyed as the <hi rend="italic">dēvadāya</hi> and <hi rend="italic">brahmadāya</hi>, for meeting the expenses of worship in the temple of Sētu-Mādhava-Perumāḷ and of repairs to the temple of Rāmanātha, both situated at Dhanushkōṭi. Half the village is said to have been granted as <hi rend="italic">tiruviḍaiyāṭṭam</hi> and half as <hi rend="italic">dēvadāṉa.</hi></p>						

						</summary>
